text: Matagari Diazasouba is a retired Côte d'Ivoire sprinter. Her biggest outing was the 2003 World Championships, where she competed in the 4 x 100 metres relay without reaching the final. She won a silver medal in the same event at the 2002 African Championships, and also finished thirteenth in the long jump there.Africathle.com ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Ivorian female sprinters Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Ivory Coast
